docs.abstract: Being part of the disability community means constantly losing friends and allies. I don’t expect that to change.
docs.snippet: Being part of the disability community means constantly losing friends and allies. I don’t expect that to change.
docs.lead_paragraph: “Kristen has passed away.” I’ll never forget learning that my best friend died. I was only 11 years old. We lived in the same town and attended school together. She had spina bifida as well as problems with her kidneys. After years of dialysis, it was kidney failure that ultimately killed Kristen.

headline.main: Even in Grief, I Still Have Pride

docs.abstract: A well-known conspiracy theorist who entered the Capitol shirtless, wearing a fur headdress with horns, was among those arrested.
docs.snippet: A well-known conspiracy theorist who entered the Capitol shirtless, wearing a fur headdress with horns, was among those arrested.
docs.lead_paragraph: A man who was photographed carrying the lectern of Speaker Nancy Pelosi during the rampage in the U.S. Capitol this week and another who roamed through the halls of Congress while wearing a horned fur headdress have been arrested and charged, the Justice Department said on Saturday.

headline.main: Trump Loyalists Arrested and Charged With Involvement in Capitol Siege

docs.abstract: The indictment marks the first charges lodged against conspirators linked to the radical gun rights group or involved with planning any of the political events held the week of the attack.
docs.snippet: The indictment marks the first charges lodged against conspirators linked to the radical gun rights group or involved with planning any of the political events held the week of the attack.
docs.lead_paragraph: Federal prosecutors filed a wide-ranging conspiracy indictment on Thursday accusing six California men said to be connected to a radical gun rights movement called the Three Percenters with plotting to assault the Capitol on Jan. 6, in the first charges lodged against anyone involved with planning any of the political events held the week of the attack.

headline.main: 6 Men Said to Be Tied to Three Percenters Movement Are Charged in Capitol Riot
headline.print_headline: 6 Tied to Gun Rights Group  Are Linked to Capitol Riot

docs.abstract: Representing 29 states and subject areas across the curriculum, these teachers will bring the mission of The Times to their schools for the 2020-21 school year.
docs.snippet: Representing 29 states and subject areas across the curriculum, these teachers will bring the mission of The Times to their schools for the 2020-21 school year.
docs.lead_paragraph: In July, we officially welcomed a distinguished group of 60 educators to The New York Times Teaching Project. Chosen from hundreds of applicants and representing 29 states, these teachers are passionate about bringing the mission of The Times — helping people understand the world through on-the-ground, expert and deeply reported independent journalism — to their school communities.

headline.main: 60 Talented Educators Join The New York Times Teaching Project

docs.abstract: Mr. Maher and his guest, Senator Ben Sasse, Republican of Nebraska, were swiftly criticized on social media after Mr. Maher’s comments were broadcast.
docs.snippet: Mr. Maher and his guest, Senator Ben Sasse, Republican of Nebraska, were swiftly criticized on social media after Mr. Maher’s comments were broadcast.
docs.lead_paragraph: The HBO late-night host Bill Maher apologized on Saturday for using a racial epithet during an interview with Senator Ben Sasse, Republican of Nebraska, on a live broadcast of his show on Friday night. HBO denounced the remark as “completely inexcusable and tasteless,” and said it would be edited out of future airings.

headline.main: Bill Maher Apologizes for Use of Racial Slur on ‘Real Time’
headline.print_headline: Maher Apologizes for Use of Racial Slur on ‘Real Time’
